                values: new object[] { new DateTime(2024, 6, 1, 9, 39, 34, 202, DateTimeKind.Utc).AddTicks(258), "<p>It was a night like any other in the post-apocalyptic world, where the undead roamed the streets, and the living huddled in fear. But little did we know that our salvation would come in the form of a beat so funky, it would shake the very foundations of the zombie apocalypse.</p><p>It all started when a group of survivors stumbled upon an abandoned disco club, its mirrored walls and glittering dance floor a stark contrast to the desolate landscape outside. As they explored the dusty interior, one brave soul cranked up the ancient sound system, and the opening notes of a classic disco anthem filled the air.</p><h3>The Rhythm of Survival</h3><p>At first, the survivors were hesitant, their bodies tense and their eyes darting towards the exits. But as the infectious groove took hold, something primal stirred within them. One by one, they began to sway, their hips swiveling in time with the pulsating beat.</p><p>Before long, the dance floor was alive with a frenzy of flailing limbs and gyrating bodies, the survivors lost in the ecstasy of movement. It was as if the music had tapped into a primordial force, a primal rhythm that transcended the boundaries of life and death.</p><h3>The Undead Can't Resist the Groove</h3><p>Little did the survivors know, their impromptu dance party had attracted the attention of a nearby horde of zombies. Drawn by the thumping bass and the infectious energy, the undead shambled towards the disco, their rotting limbs twitching in an eerie parody of dance.</p><p>As the first zombies stumbled through the doors, the survivors froze, their hearts pounding in their chests. But then, something miraculous happened. The zombies, their decaying bodies swaying in time with the music, began to mimic the survivors' dance moves.</p><p>At first, it was a clumsy, jerky imitation, but as the beat pulsed through their undead veins, the zombies'